byline: By Arnaud Leparmentier (San Francisco (United States) correspondent)

title: Trump posthumously honors 'martyr' Charlie Kirk with the Presidential Medal of Freedom
subhed: Tuesday's ceremony coincided with what would have been Kirk’s 32nd birthday, just over a month after the right-wing activist was fatally shot while speaking to a crowd at Utah Valley University. Meanwhile, the US State Department said it had revoked visas of at least six foreign nationals who had 'celebrated the heinous assassination.'

title: First Wap, a discreet cyber-surveillance firm tracking journalists, public figures and corporate executives
subhed: Little known to the public, this long-standing player in the surveillance industry has been selling phone-tracking technology for more than 20 years, including to authoritarian regimes. Among its targets: a journalist investigating the Vatican, an Airbus employee, and Hollywood actor Jared Leto.
